      "ADS camera anchor is present."
    ],
    "warnings": [
      "No material table; current build relies on vertex colors only.",
      "No NORMAL attributes found; shading will rely on importer/engine fallback or flat/unlit rendering.",
      "No UVs found; fine for vertex-color prototypes, limiting for production skins/camos/decals.",
      "All sockets/parts are direct children of the root; this is simple, but sockets on animated modules should be parented to the moving part.",
      "Socket nodes currently provide positions but no distinct orientation frames.",
      "Primary grip socket name is right-hand-specific; this makes left-hand/dual-wield support harder.",
      "Pistol support point is a generic support marker near the magazine floor; off-hand semantics should be explicit.",
      "Geometry is embedded as many tiny base64 buffers in a JSON .gltf; usable, but not ideal for production/runtime packs."
    ],
    "recommendedChanges": [
      "Add stable named PBR/unlit materials even if the art stays simple, so runtime and editor tooling can address parts by material.",
      "Export normals for production weapons; add tangents if normal maps are added.",
      "Parent moving-part sockets to the moving part they belong to, such as slide/ejection/magazine/charging-handle sockets.",
      "Author sockets as full transforms, not only points; grip, support, optic, holster, and melee sockets need meaningful rotation axes.",
      "Rename/export canonical `grip.primary` and use manifest fields for preferred/allowed hands.",
      "Represent pistol off-hand as `supportPolicy: optional_palm_overlay`, not as a hard support grip.",
      "Publish runtime weapons as .glb or as .gltf + a single .bin; keep source scenes separate."
    ],
    "artistNotes": [
      "Keep slide/barrel/frame/grip separation; add magazine/ejection sockets if reload/fire cycles matter.",
      "Treat support as optional palm overlay rather than a true foregrip.",
      "Remove hand side from the canonical grip socket name; express handedness in manifest."
    ]
